title: Short Poetry Collection 117
description:
LibriVox's Short Poetry Collection 117. This is a collection of 21 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for February 2013. This project contains the following: A Prayer by Anne Bronte (1820 -1849) Be Drunken by Charles Baudelaire (1821-1867) Translated by Arthur Symons (1865-1945) Brothers by James Weldon Johnson (1871-1938) The Contrast by Helen Gray Cone (1859-1934) The Cynic by Theodosia Garrison (1874-1944) Do You Ever Feel Like God? by Christopher Morley (1890-1957) Do you Fear the Wind? by Hamlin Garland (1860-1940) God's Grandeur by Gerard Manley Hopkins (1844-1889) Haunted by Don Marquis (1878-1937) In the Park by Helen Hoyt (1887-1972) The Isle of Lost Dreams by William Sharp (1855-1905) The Lost Path by Elinor Wylie (1885-1928) My Life is like the Summer Rose by Richard Henry Wilde (1789-1847) Nevertheless by Clifford Franklin Gessler (1893-?) Protest by Ella Wheeler Wilcox (1850â1919) Service by Anna Hempstead Branch (1875-1937) Sestina of the Tramp Royal by Rudyard Kipling (1865-1936) Solitude and the Lily by Richard Henry Horne (1802â1884) The Fool by Robert W Service (1874-1915) Tom Merritt by Edgar Lee Masters (1868â1950) Where's the Poker? by Christopher Smart (1722-1771) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
